Subject: GetDepartmentCodes
Description: Gets the accounting departments for a dealership.
Request Parameters: Name: companyId, Type: integer, Description: ID of the company/dealership, Required/Optional: Required
Response Structure: Collection of Department objects. Each Department object has: DepartmentCode (string), Description (string), Placement (CompanyPlacement object). The CompanyPlacement object has: CompanyId (integer), CompanyName (string), SourceId (integer), DealerId (integer), EnvironmentId (integer), EnvironmentType (DataEnvironmentType enum), GroupId (integer), GroupName (string). The DataEnvironmentType enum has possible values: Undefined (0), Production (1), Testing (2), Staging (3).
Sample Response: Not available

Subject: PullCustomerKeys
Description: Pulls API CustomerKeys matching a search.
Request Parameters:
- ActivityStoreIds: Collection of integer
- PartialName: string
- Phone: string
- DriverLicenseNumber: string
- CustomerNumber: string
- MaximumUpdateStamp: date
- MinimumUpdateStamp: date
- SourceIds: Collection of integer (Required)
- MaxElapsedSinceUpdate: time interval (Filter records that have been created or modified between the difference of now and this. PullRepairOrders Notice: The length of time allowed is limited to 32 days.)
- ChangedPeriodStart: date (Filter records that have been created or modified starting with this. Note: ChangedPeriodStart is not used by PullRepairOrders)
- ChangedPeriodEnd: date (Filter records that have been created or modified ending with this. Note: ChangedPeriodEnd is not used by PullRepairOrders)
- SuppressErrors: boolean (If an error occurs in a multi-dealer pull, continue pulling from other dealers instead of failing the whole request.)
Response Structure:
Collection of CustomerSummary
- CustomerKey: string
- ModifiedStamp: date
- Placement: SourcePlacement
  - GroupId: int
  - GroupName: string
Sample Response:
<ArrayOfCustomerSummary xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/DealerBuilt.BaseApi">
  <CustomerSummary>
    <CustomerKey>string</CustomerKey>
    <ModifiedStamp>date</ModifiedStamp>
    <Placement>
      <GroupId>int</GroupId>
      <GroupName>string</GroupName>
    </Placement>
  </CustomerSummary>
</ArrayOfCustomerSummary>

Subject: PullProspects
Description: Pulls sales prospects (buyers) matching a search.

[ProspectSearchCriteria]()
| Name | Description | Type | Additional information |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| PartialName | string |
| Phone | string |
| DriverLicenseNumber | string |
| StoreIds | Collection of integer | Required |
| MaxElapsedSinceUpdate | Filter records that have been created or modified between the difference of now and this | time interval |
| ChangedPeriodStart | Filter records that have been created or modified starting with this | date |
| ChangedPeriodEnd | Filter records that have been created or modified ending with this | date |
| SuppressErrors | If an error occurs in a multi-dealer pull, continue pulling from other dealers instead of failing the whole request. | boolean |

Collection of [Prospect]()
| Name | Description | Type | Additional information |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| DealKey | string |
| Attributes | [IdentityProfile]() |

| ErrorMessage | string |
| PhysicalAddress | Physical address also known as garaging address. | [Address]() |

| Placement | [StorePlacement]() |

Subject: PushDeals
Description: Pushes deal structure and cobuyers. Adds additional data to the record created by PushProspects.
Request Parameters:
StoreId (integer): API identifier of the store for this deal. Required
DealKey (string): The API DealKey of an existing Prospect/Deal to update. To get the DealKey, either: (1) create a new Prospect with PushProspects and use the PushedRecordKey from the push response as DealKey; or (2) call PullDeals and use the DealKey from the pull response to update an existing Deal. Required
InventoryKey (string): API identifier of the stock vehicle. Use either InventoryKey or StockNumber to assign a vehicle.
StockNumber (string): Dealer stock number of the stock vehicle. Use either InventoryKey or StockNumber to assign a vehicle.
CustomerDriverLicense (DriversLicense): 
TradeIns (Collection of TradeInPushRequest): Trade-in numbers for this deal: allowance, ACV, and payoff. To push trade vehicle data, use PushAppraisals.
ExternalDealId (string): Optional integrator identifier for this record. The ExternalProspectId is echoed in the push response, but isn't stored. When pushing multiple records in one request, it can be useful for matching push responses to push requests.
SalesNumber (string): Employee number of the sales person.
SalesNumber2 (string): Employee number of the second sales person.
SalesManagerNumber (string): Employee number of the sales manager.
Cobuyer (CobuyerInfo): Cobuyer's personal information.
DealType (DealType): Deal type: lease, finance, cash, etc.
Msrp (MonetaryValue): Manufacturer's suggested retail price. If null or zero, the MSRP is calculated from the SellingPrice: MSRP = SellingPrice - HardAdds. If both MSRP and SellingPrice are populated, the deal's discount is calculated as: Discount = (MSRP + HardAdds - SellingPrice) * -1.
SellingPrice (MonetaryValue): Selling price. Includes hard adds (sum of DealPushRequest.HardAdds.Price). Does not include soft adds, incentives, rebates, insurance products, or other products. If both MSRP and SellingPrice are populated, the deal's discount is calculated as: Discount = (MSRP + HardAdds - SellingPrice) * -1.
TaxableSalesAmount (MonetaryValue): 
CashDownPayment (MonetaryValue): 
Lease (LeaseInfo): Deal structure and tax/fee data for lease deals.
Finance (BuyInfo): Deal structure and tax/fee data for retail deals.
ContractDate (date): 
TermMonths (integer): Finance/lease term in months.
Rate (decimal number): Interest rate percent, formatted like "16.9". For finance, flex-buy, and balloon deals.
BuyRate (decimal number): Buy rate percent, formatted like "16.9". For finance, flex-buy, and balloon deals.
DaysToFirstPayment (integer): Days from contract date to first payment date. For finance, flex-buy, and balloon deals. If zero, the value is taken from the store's setup for new Deal records and unchanged for existing Deal records.
ResidualPercentage (decimal number): Residual percentage, formatted like "59.5".
ResidualAmount (MonetaryValue): 
BaseResidualAmount (MonetaryValue): 
LenderCode (string): Dealer-defined code for the lender.
SoftAdds (Collection of SoftAdd): Non-residualized accessories.
HardAdds (Collection of HardAdd): Residualized accessories.
Rebates (Collection of Rebate): 
ServiceContracts (Collection of SaleServiceContract): 
Incentives (Collection of Incentive): 
MileageResidualAdjustPercent (decimal number): 
EstimatedPayment (MonetaryValue): 
Mrm (MonetaryValue): Maximum Residualized MSRP.
InsuranceProducts (Collection of InsuranceProduct): 
WaiveFeesAndTaxes (boolean): Is the dealer waiving fees and taxes for this Deal?
FinanceCharge (MonetaryValue): 
FinanceManagerNumbers (Collection of string): Employee numbers of the finance managers. Max length: 2
PrepaidFinanceChargeAmount (MonetaryValue): 
ProtectionPackages (Collection of ProtectionPackage): 
ReturnDealFlag (boolean): 
VehicleId (integer): 
ProductDetails (ServiceProduct): 
FinanceReserve (MonetaryValue):
Response Structure:
ExternalRecordId (string)
Message (string)
PushedDeal (PushedDeal)
PushedRecordKey (string)
PushResult (PushResult)
StoreId (integer)

Subject: PushProspects
Description: Pushes sales prospects (buyers). PushProspects is the first step of creating a deal.
Request Parameters:
DealKey (string): The API DealKey of an existing Prospect/Deal to update, or null/blank to create a new prospect. The Prospect and Deal records will have a same DealKey.
CustomerKey (string): Customer Key for this prospect.
StoreId (integer): API identifier of the store for this prospect. Required.
ExternalProspectId (string): Optional integrator identifier for this record. The ExternalProspectId is echoed in the push response, but isn't stored. When pushing multiple records in one request, it can be useful for matching push responses to push requests.
Identity (IdentityProfile): Buyer's contact information.
License (DriversLicense): Buyer's driver's license number.
SalesNumber (string): Employee numbers of the sales person.
ProspectSource (string): The way the prospect came into the store: walk-in, phone, internet, etc. To get the list of valid prospect sources for this store, call GetStoreSetups.
AdvertisingSource (string): The advertising channel that brought in the prospect. To get the list of valid advertising sources for this store, call GetStoreSetups.
PhysicalAddress (Address): Physical address also known as garaging address.
PhysicalDamageInsurance (PhysicalDamageInsurance): Physical damage insurance (PDI).
Response Structure:
StoreId (integer)
PushedDeal (Deal)
PushedRecordKey (string)
PushResult (PushResult)
Message (string)
ExternalRecordId (string)
Sample Response: Not available

Subject: PushSalesPrice
Description: Update SalesPrice based on StockID/ StockNumber/ VIN.
Request Parameters: InventoryKey (string), StoreId (integer), ExternalVehicleId (string), Vin (string), SalesPriceAttributes (SalesPriceAttributes), StockNumber (string), UniqueId (integer). SalesPriceAttributes contains: AdvertisedSalePrice (Amount, Currency), BaseMsrp (Amount, Currency), DealerDefinedStatus (string), ExplodeVin (boolean), FloorAmount (Amount, Currency), InvoiceNumberString (string), ModifiedBy (string), ModifiedStamp (datetime), Msrp (Amount, Currency), Price (Amount, Currency), StockDataAttributes (EstimatedArrivalDate, OrderCustomerId, OrderDate, OrderDetail, OrderNumber), StockNumber (string), WholeSalePrice (decimal). Amount (decimal), Currency (string).
Response Structure: VehicleKey (string), InventoryKey (string), StockNumber (string), StoreId (integer), PushedDeal (Deal), PushedRecordKey (string), PushResult (PushResult), Message (string), ExternalRecordId (string). Deal contains: DealId (string), DealNumber (string), DealStatus (string), DealType (string), TotalAmount (decimal). - ServiceLocationName (string)
- StoreId (integer)
- StoreName (string)
- CompanyId (integer)
- CompanyName (string)
- SourceId (integer)
- DealerId (integer)
- EnvironmentId (integer)
- EnvironmentType (DataEnvironmentType object)
- GroupId (integer)
- GroupName (string)

MonetaryValue object has the following structure:
- Currency (CurrencyType object)
- Amount (decimal number)

CurrencyType is an enumeration with the following possible values:
- UsDollar (0)
- Euro (1)
- EnglishPound (2)
- CanadianDollar (3)

DataEnvironmentType is an enumeration with the following possible values:
- Undefined (0)
- Production (1)
- Testing (2)
- Staging (3)

PartsOrderType is an enumeration with the following possible values:
- Unknown (0)
- Stock (65)
- Special (83)

- RemoteDrop (86)
- Supplemental (85)
- LexDpo (88)
- Overnight (79)
- Holiday (72)
- LargeDealerOrder (76)
- Solicited (78)
- TransientOwner (73)
- Campaign (67)
- ASRReturn (82)
- ASRStockOrder (89)
- NonASRReturn (90)

Subject: PushDeferredLaborItems
Description: Pushes deferred (customer-declined) labor items.
Request Parameters: The request is a collection of PotentialLaborItemPushRequest. Each PotentialLaborItemPushRequest has: ServiceLocationId (integer), JobKey (string), LaborItem (PushedPotentialLaborItemAttributes). PushedPotentialLaborItemAttributes has: ExternalLaborItemId (string), Code (string), Hours (decimal number), OtherLaborHours (decimal number), LaborRate (MonetaryValue), LaborAmount (MonetaryValue), LaborTax (MonetaryValue), Remark (string), FailCode (string), LaborType (string), Description (string), LineNumber (integer), IsApproved (boolean), Cause (string), Correction (string), LaborPriceCode (string), Sublets (Collection of PushedPotentialLaborOperationSubletAttributes). MonetaryValue has: Currency (CurrencyType), Amount (decimal number). CurrencyType has possible enumeration values: UsDollar (0), Euro (1), EnglishPound (2), CanadianDollar (3). PushedPotentialLaborOperationSubletAttributes has: Cost (MonetaryValue), Description (string), ExternalSubletId (string), InvoiceNumber (string), SalePrice (MonetaryValue), Tax (MonetaryValue).
Response Structure: The response is a collection of PotentialLaborItemPushResponse. Each PotentialLaborItemPushResponse has: ServiceLocationId (integer), JobKey (string), ExternalLaborOperationId (string), Result (PushResult), Message (string), Sublets (Collection of PushResponse). PushResult has possible enumeration values: Unprocessed (0), Error (1), Created (2), Updated (3), Deleted (4), Processed (5). PushResponse has: PushedRecordKey (string), PushResult (PushResult), Message (string), ExternalRecordId (string).
Sample Response: Not available
